The paper focuses on visual-semantic embedding, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel multi-head self-attention network, which falls under the category of deep learning and neural networks, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely category. The paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results, indicating a focus on performance evaluation, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval and multimodal learning, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
